OL,5,Cdocs
OL,7,FThe British Medical Association NI
OL,8,Fsaid: "It is the responsibility of
OL,9,Femployers to ensure services are
OL,10,Fadequately staffed on strike days and
OL,11,FTrusts were given appropriate notice
OL,12,Fby the BMA to allow them to do so.
OL,14,F"Consultants support their junior
OL,15,Fdoctor colleagues in their industrial
OL,16,Faction, but when they provide cover,
OL,17,Fthis is in addition to their regular
OL,18,Fresponsibilities. It is therefore
OL,19,Fentirely appropriate that they are
OL,20,Fcompensated for this extra work."
